== Overview ==
The '''''Bubble-Head Charm''''' makes a pocket of breathable air about the caster's head.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
This charm has been seen used in two places so far.
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']], [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Cedric Diggory|Cedric]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Fleur Delacour|Fleur]] use the Bubble-Head Charm in the Second Task. This charm allows them to survive underwater, giving them breathing air, for the time necessary to carry out their task.
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Order of the Phoenix|''Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix'']], after [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Dolores Umbridge|Dolores Umbridge]] is appointed Headmaster, discipline at the school falls apart. Because she is afraid that the teachers might act to undermine her, Umbridge basically removes any authority they have, which leaves her and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Argus Filch|Filch]] the impossible task of maintaining discipline in a school of possibly 680 adolescent witches and wizards. While teachers can maintain order in their individual classrooms, nobody will take responsibility for the hallways, which become littered with <!-- should we include [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Dungbomb|dungbombs]] in Magic? they seem t be fully defined by their name -->dungbombs, which Filch, being a [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Squib|Squib]], is largely powerless to clean up. It becomes common practice for the students to use a Bubble-Head Charm on themselves between classes, because the hallways smell so bad.
