== About ==

Welcome to my Gadgets page. My gadgets are tools that I've created for helping to automate complex tasks, especially tasks related to creating a new book here on Wikibooks. Gadgets can be viewed and used on the [[User:Whiteknight/Book Creator|Book Creator]] page. The links below will take you to the source code for these gadgets. Documentation is linked to from the Book Creator.

{{TextBox|<center><big>'''Installation Instructions'''</big></center>

All stable scripts are now available as Gadgets. Manual install is not necessary. To install my most popular scripts, follow these instructions:
# Go to [[Special:Preferences]]
# Click the '''Gadgets''' tab
# Check the box next to "'''Whiteknight's Visual Book Designer'''"
This will automatically install several scripts, including my '''Visual Book Designer''' and '''Book Creator''' scripts. All scripts, once installed, can be used at the '''[[User:Whiteknight/Book Creator|Book Creator]]''' page. 
}}

=== Status ===

*All scripts are tested to work in '''FireFox 2''' and '''FireFox 3'''.
*Support for '''IE7''' and '''IE6''' is good but not robustly tested. Plus, I have to do some ugly hack work to make these browsers work the same as FireFox. 
*'''Opera''', '''Safari''' and '''Chrome''' should work for most things, but are not regularly tested.

== Main Scripts ==
{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|myskin.js}}
:My master javascript, handles the includes for all the other scripts listed below.

{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|monobook.js}}
:My old master javascript. Deprecated.

{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|gadgetscore.js}}
:{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|Gadgetscore|Documentation}}
:The basic framework script that all my gadgets rely on. All my gadgets require this script to function. 

{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|gadgets.js}}
:Javascript to automatically include my gadgets core and all my best gadgets. To install, add this to your [[Special:MyPage/monobook.js|personal javascript file]]:

 import_script('User:Whiteknight/gadgets.js');

{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|jquery.js}}
:The JQuery framework, which I am going to be using in lieu of my gadgetscore script for all future work.

{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|perpage.js}}
:{{User:Whiteknight/Page2|Perbook|Documentation}}
:Enables me to load per-book javascript and CSS files. For a list of all books i use this functionality on, see [[User:Whiteknight/Per Page|Per Page]]. Dopes not currently work in IE with any reliability.

